[13]
The applicant's counsel attacked the decision in a variety of ways. She submits the tribunal erred:
(1) In not granting the applicant a hearing since his credibility was impugned;
(2) There were serious administrative delays in the handling of his file that make it extraordinary;
(3) He had vested rights as a PRDCC claimant;
(4) The PRRA Officer misconstrued or ignored relevant evidence.
IV.
Analysis and Conclusions
